(48, 37, 36, 'Song of Someone Else Song of Someone Else Song of Someone Else Song of Someone Else Song of Someone Else Song of Someone Else', 'I long for the music of tomorrow \r\nfrom the rendezvous between two sights,\r\nlike a diamond \r\nperfect bond and beauty.\r\n\r\nI can hear God laughing\r\nand the universe slowly dying\r\nwith paradise hanging over my head.\r\n\r\nI have watered the Earth with your song\r\nempty of your music \r\nbut surrounded by its light,\r\nI have salted the dust but born an Eden.\r\n\r\nThis is your song,\r\nlistening to the whispers of the water\r\nin a hollow seashell yearning for an ocean\r\nthat was never present.I long for the music of tomorrow \r\nfrom the rendezvous between two sights,\r\nlike a diamond \r\nperfect bond and beauty.\r\n\r\nI can hear God laughing\r\nand the universe slowly dying\r\nwith paradise hanging over my head.\r\n\r\nI have watered the Earth with your song\r\nempty of your music \r\nbut surrounded by its light,\r\nI have salted the dust but born an Eden.\r\n\r\nThis is your song,\r\nlistening to the whispers of the water\r\nin a hollow seashell yearning for an ocean\r\nthat was never present.', 'I long for the music of tomorrow \r\nfrom the rendezvous between two sights,\r\nlike a diamond \r\nperfect bond and beauty.\r\n\r\nI can hear God laughing\r\nand the universe slowly dying\r\nwith paradise hanging over my head.\r\n\r\nI have watered the Earth with your song\r\nempty of your music \r\nbut surrounded by its light,\r\nI have salted the dust but born an Eden.\r\n\r\nThis is your song,\r\nlistening to the whispers of the water\r\nin a hollow seashell yearning for an ocean\r\nthat was never present.I long for the music of tomorrow \r\nfrom the rendezvous between two sights,\r\nlike a diamond \r\nperfect bond and beauty.\r\n\r\nI can hear God laughing\r\nand the universe slowly dying\r\nwith paradise hanging over my head.\r\n\r\nI have watered the Earth with your song\r\nempty of your music \r\nbut surrou